@dwallacewells Chinse coal use did not fall last year.

Its use in electricity generation in China dropped, but that was offset by other uses (notably, coal-to-chemicals). Overall, Chinese coal consumption in 2025 was largely flat y-on-y (up ~0.3%).

Some extra context: China consumed ~92.2 EJ of coal last year (that's ~55% of global demand); the US consumed ~8.7 EJ (~5% of global demand).
